node.text: I really want people to understand how much of an opportunity there is out here for people with conviction, will, gusto, appetite … because this garage sale flip life shit is game changing, I get emails daily from people who started it and are stunned where they are a year later starting with only $200 … #TrashTalk episode 6 is coming shortly but here is a preview of my best moment. After going ice 🧊 cold 🥶 for 2-3 hours and getting literally nothing in the first 20 sales .. I hit a mother load of Manga Japanese books 📚 for $270 that will go bananas 🍌 on EBay ✅… y’all can do it … please get yours

node.text:
Leave the story of what happened in the comments 

Late last night I texted an older friend and it was the best feeling 

Life is about relationships and many of you should just call an old pal 

I know there will be jokes about X’s ect and all that “hahaha shit” but maybe one person will  reconnect with a parent, sibling, former best friend.

Some of you lost top people because of a silly fight and your inability to be the bigger person, you allowed your insecurities to win and lose out on a relationship that mattered to you. Use this short clip as a sign that today is a day to reconnect ❤️❤️❤️❤️

Love always wins, hate or darkness is a trick

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gary Vay-Ner-Chuk in Hudson Yards New York. May be an image of 8 people, people standing and text that says 'sg PELOTON'.

node.text:
Be kind ❤️

Gave away all the #MangaBooks I got in TrashTalk episode 6 (link to episode in bio) to people who on 49 minutes noticed showed up outside my office.

I hope many of them flip these books and turn it into a jump start

It was also beyond nice to see so many of you who consume the work and enjoy being part of this community

You can do a lot more by doing things vs talking about how bad / unfair things are .. big shout out to those who took action today … ❤️❤️❤️❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gary Vay-Ner-Chuk on July 18, 2021. May be an illustration.

node.text:
Sunday morning comic brought to you by @veefriends 
Every #EntrepreneurElf needs a #DrivenDragon to wake them up in the “micro moments” to many of you this morning are worried and dwelling when in reality it’s only a small % into your journey, I’ve had really bad days, weeks, months even in business, it’s part of the process, I’ve had less productive years, projects, business relationships … it’s all part of the journey … take a breathe and look up and understand where you are in the “macro”

node.text: I could have had millions more subscribers and awareness and brand building if I had stayed on YouTube in 2007-2011 … but I didn’t .. I didn’t 😭 cry … I adjusted and moved forward and didn’t make the mistake again (never pick $ over awareness/brand building, more eye balls 👀 ) and I was also accountable and knew … I made the mistake .. no one else, I didn’t look to blame .. ❤️❤️❤️
